'''Proration''' is used in [[telecommunication]] and in [[insurance]].

==Telecommunication==
Proration, or budgeting, is the proportional distribution or allocation of parameters, such as [[noise power]] and [[transmission (telecommunications)|transmission]] losses, among a number of [[tandem]]-connected items, such as equipment, cables, links, or trunks, in order to balance the performance of [[information transfer|communications]] circuits. 

In a telephone [[switching center]], proration is the distribution or allocation of equipment or components proportionally among a number of functions, to provide a requisite [[grade of service]]. 

